- Part-time Associate Professor.  
- Program Co-director for Master IMSA (*Ingénierie Mathématiques et Statistiques Actuarielles*).

**Master 2 IMSA Courses:**  
- *Modelling and Valuation of Insurance Products*: theoretical lectures and practical work on building models (BE & PVFP) in Non-Life — Health, Disability, and Life insurance (30h).  
- Excel & VBA: functionalities, functions, and programming (20h).  
- Python for actuarial science.  
- Data Science for actuarial science: data processing, exploratory analysis, machine learning, data visualization.

**Master 1 IMSA Courses:**  
- Life Insurance Actuarial Science: guarantees, technical tools, pricing, and reserving (15h).  
- Actuarial Statistics: technical introduction to actuarial science (20h), non-life pricing.  
- Introduction to Python for data processing.  
- Professionalization module: actuarial career presentations, CV and cover letter preparation, mock interviews, seminar organization.
